<item>
            <title>[LU-614] Speed up test scripts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-614</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Fixes to speed up the Lustre internal test scripts in order improve testing efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a starter, conf-sanity test_54&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ab&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; are taking 30 minutes together to do very low-value testing of the llverdev and llverfs scripts (e.g. &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/ff31e77a-ca79-11e0-8d02-52540025f9af&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/ff31e77a-ca79-11e0-8d02-52540025f9af&lt;/a&gt;).  It is important to verify those scripts work, but they should only ever do partial testing in conf-sanity, and full runs are usually only done in a separate &quot;large-LUN&quot; test.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="11538">LU-614</key>
